            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>9&#47;17   85<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev and dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your note of to day I receive in this mo&#45;<lb/>ment&#91;.&#93; In answer I beg leave to state I can<lb/> not understand the purpose to make again<lb/> a memorial service. We honored the great<lb/> dead publicly last year. We lamented<lb/> the lose<sic></sic> in the synagogues when we learned<lb/> of his demise. Now it is jewish principle<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; &#91;&#63;&#93; &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> The dead need &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> not our interference before the all  mighty<lb/> such memorials&#8212;after what was done has<lb/>&#45;&#45; for me of least&#45;&#45;a seeming of imitation of <lb/> what passes in Christian churches. Yours<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. Hirsch<lb/></p>
            </body>
